Every morning for the past 30 years, Thorvaldur Gunnlaugsson has risen early and sailed out of Reykjavik harbour at 4.30 am to fish in the freezing waters off the coast of Iceland – returning with his small boat laden with plaice, tusk fish and haddock.

But this summer he plans to try something new. "I'm going to go for mackerel," said Mr Gunnlaugsson, 48, as his five-metre long boat smashed through the wind-whipped seas last
